          >
            BH Macro PMs Land New Roles
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="EB Garamond" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6">
            Three former Portfolio Managers in Brevan Howard’s systematic macro
            team, who left the $35bn Jersey-headquartered global macro hedge
            fund firm earlier this year, have found new homes. Michael Krupin, a
            former G10 FX trader at Barclays who spent a year at Brevan Howard
            between May 2023 and May 2024, has joined
            <a
              href="https://www.efinancialcareers.com/news/hedge-fund-brevan-howard-s-macro-portfolio-managers-are-resurfacing"
              target="_blank"
              >First New York</a
            >. This multi-strategy investment firm provides trading
            infrastructure for experienced portfolio managers.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider
