        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Verdana" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700">
            BlackRock Explores Buying HPS Investment Partners
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="EB Garamond" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6">
            BlackRock is exploring the potential acquisition of HPS Investment
            Partners, which could position it among the top players in the
            private credit market. HPS, also considering an initial public
            offering (IPO) valued at over $10 billion, has been in talks with
            BlackRock and other potential buyers, including CVC Capital
            Partners. A deal has
            <a
              href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-09/blackrock-among-suitors-said-to-explore-buying-credit-firm-hps"
              target="_blank"
              >yet to be finalized</a
            >, and discussions may end with an agreement. BlackRock, aiming to
            expand in alternative assets, has already completed two acquisitions
            this year. Private credit is experiencing rapid growth, with major
            players like Apollo and JPMorgan Chase making similar moves.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
